   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Save Infant Lives with Breast-Feeding Education</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Breast-feeding can save 1 million infant lives a year. DocImpact uses a film screening &amp; workshop model to reach health-workers in areas with high infant mortality rates. In partnership with local healthcare NGOs, each screening&amp;workshop educates 30 health-workers with a reach of 450 expectant mothers in rural Kenya. Due to the success of the first project and high demand, the scheme is being expanded to ensure each mother is monitored and supported for the first 2 years of the infant&apos;s life.</narrative>
  </description>
